SIMPLE: overmatch
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overmatch
<hw>O`ver*match"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
be more than equal to or a match for; hence, to vanquish.</def>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To marry (one) to a superior.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overmatch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overmatch
<hw>O"ver*match`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One superior in
power; also, an unequal match; a contest in which one of the opponents
is overmatched.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au> <au>D. Webster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overmeasure</ent>⟦br⟧
